  "prompt": "Will 8 RAC tickets that have changed to CNF, get adjacent berths?",
  "response": "In Indian Railways, if you have 8 RAC (Reservation Against Cancellation) tickets that have been converted to CNF (Confirmed), there is no guarantee that you will get adjacent berths. The allotment of berths depends on the availability of seats in the coach and the seat allocation system used by Indian Railways.\n\nIn general, Indian Railways tries to accommodate passengers with RAC tickets in a way that families or groups traveling together get adjacent berths, but this isn't always possible due to the configuration of the train and the specific allotment rules. If all 8 passengers have RAC tickets converting to CNF in a single transaction, the chances of getting adjacent berths may be higher compared to if they were booked separately.\n\nFor the most accurate information and to increase your chances of getting adjacent berths, it\u2019s recommended to book tickets together and check your PNR after the confirmation phase.",
